\hypertarget{stable-names}{%
\section{\texorpdfstring{Stable
Names\protect\hyperlink{stable-names}{}}{Stable Names}}\label{stable-names}}

Stable names are written as
\VERB|\OperatorTok{[}\NormalTok{basic}\OperatorTok{.}\NormalTok{life}\OperatorTok{]\{.}\NormalTok{sref}\OperatorTok{\}}|
, and renders as {6.8.4
\href{https://wg21.link/basic.life}{{[}basic.life{]}}}. You can also add
a class
\VERB|\OperatorTok{{-}}|
or
\VERB|\OperatorTok{.}\NormalTok{unnumbered}|
to omit the section number.

It uses \url{https://timsong-cpp.github.io/cppwp/annex-f} as the
underlying database.

Examples:

\begin{longtable}[]{@{}
  >{\raggedright\arraybackslash}p{(\columnwidth - 2\tabcolsep) * \real{0.5811}}
  >{\raggedright\arraybackslash}p{(\columnwidth - 2\tabcolsep) * \real{0.4189}}@{}}
\toprule()
\begin{minipage}[b]{\linewidth}\raggedright
\centering\arraybackslash\textbf{Source Text}
\end{minipage} & \begin{minipage}[b]{\linewidth}\raggedright
\centering\arraybackslash\textbf{Rendered}
\end{minipage} \\
\midrule()
\endhead

\VERB|\NormalTok{[basic.life]\{.sref\}}|
& {6.8.4
\href{https://wg21.link/basic.life}{{[}basic.life{]}}} \\

\VERB|\NormalTok{[basic.life\#1]\{.sref\}}|
& {6.8.4
\href{https://wg21.link/basic.life\#1}{{[}basic.life\#1{]}}} \\

\VERB|\NormalTok{[basic.life]\{{-} .sref\}}|
& {\href{https://wg21.link/basic.life}{{[}basic.life{]}}} \\

\VERB|\NormalTok{[basic.life]\{.unnumbered .sref\}}|
& {\href{https://wg21.link/basic.life}{{[}basic.life{]}}} \\
\bottomrule()
\end{longtable}

\hypertarget{notes}{%
\section{\texorpdfstring{Notes\protect\hyperlink{notes}{}}{Notes}}\label{notes}}

There are three supported styles of note:

\begin{itemize}
\item
  Use the
  \VERB|\NormalTok{note}|
  class for notes that are expected to appear in the specification
  wording

  \begin{Shaded}
  \begin{Highlighting}[]
  \NormalTok{[Notes will look like this]\{.note\}}
  \end{Highlighting}
  \end{Shaded}

  {{{[} \emph{Note:} }Notes will look like
  this{ --- \emph{end note} {]}}}
\item
  Use the
  \VERB|\NormalTok{ednote}|
  for editorial notes, these will be formatted as

  \begin{Shaded}
  \begin{Highlighting}[]
  \NormalTok{[Editorial notes are important]\{.ednote\}}
  \end{Highlighting}
  \end{Shaded}

  {{\color[HTML]{0000ff}{[} Editor's note: Editorial notes are
  important {]}}}
\item
  Use
  \VERB|\NormalTok{draftnote}|
  to include text that is intended as questions or information for
  reviews and working groups.

  \begin{Shaded}
  \begin{Highlighting}[]
  \NormalTok{[Drafting notes can be used to provide comments for reviewers that are explicitly not to be}
  \NormalTok{ included in the specification.]\{.draftnote\}}

  \NormalTok{ [It is also possible to indicate the a note is for}
  \NormalTok{ a specific \textasciigrave{}audience\textasciigrave{} via this optional attribute.]\{.draftnote audience="the reader"\}}
  \end{Highlighting}
  \end{Shaded}

  {{\color[HTML]{0000ff}{[} Drafting note: Drafting notes can be used to
  provide comments for reviewers that are explicitly not to be included
  in the specification. {]}}}

  {{\color[HTML]{0000ff}{[} Drafting note for the reader: It is also
  possible to indicate the a note is for a specific
  \VERB|\NormalTok{audience}|
  via this optional attribute. {]}}}
\end{itemize}

\hypertarget{citation}{%
\section{\texorpdfstring{Citation\protect\hyperlink{citation}{}}{Citation}}\label{citation}}

Automatic references are written as
\VERB|\OperatorTok{[@}\NormalTok{N4762}\OperatorTok{]}|
and renders as \href{https://wg21.link/n4762}{{[}N4762{]}}. Anything in
\url{https://wg21.link/index.yaml} are linked automatically.

\begin{itemize}
\tightlist
\item

  \VERB|\NormalTok{N}|
  Papers (e.g.,
  \VERB|\OperatorTok{[@}\NormalTok{N3887}\OperatorTok{]}|
  → \href{https://wg21.link/n3887}{{[}N3887{]}})
\item

  \VERB|\NormalTok{P}|
  Papers (e.g.,
  \VERB|\OperatorTok{[@}\NormalTok{P1371R1}\OperatorTok{]}|
  → \href{https://wg21.link/p1371r1}{{[}P1371R1{]}})
\item
  CWG Issues (e.g.,
  \VERB|\OperatorTok{[@}\NormalTok{CWG1234}\OperatorTok{]}|
  → \href{https://wg21.link/cwg1234}{{[}CWG1234{]}})
\item
  LWG Issues (e.g.,
  \VERB|\OperatorTok{[@}\NormalTok{LWG1234}\OperatorTok{]}|
  → \href{https://wg21.link/lwg1234}{{[}LWG1234{]}})
\item
  Github Edits (e.g,
  \VERB|\OperatorTok{[@}\NormalTok{EDIT1234}\OperatorTok{]}|
  → \href{https://wg21.link/edit1234}{{[}EDIT1234{]}})
\item
  Standing Documents (e.g.,
  \VERB|\OperatorTok{[@}\NormalTok{SD6}\OperatorTok{]}|
  → \href{https://wg21.link/sd6}{{[}SD6{]}})
\end{itemize}

You may also write
\VERB|\NormalTok{[@P2996R8]\{.title\}}| to include the title of the
paper, and renders as: {\href{https://wg21.link/p2996r8}{{[}P2996R8{]}
(Reflection for C++26)}}.

